raw_data.title: Web Operations Engineer (WebOps)
raw_data.description: Collaborates  with software developers, system operators and other IT staff members to manage reliability of web-based cloud applications. Implement site reliability engineering best-practices as they relate to web-based applications.  Designs, plans, tests, monitors, and maintains application and infrastructure-level systems for delivering web-based services. Oversees installation, provisioning, configuration, operation and maintenance of required hardware and software related to cloud computing infrastructure components. Provides guidance and sets standards on operating internal and external organizational projects to a cloud computing environment including migration of existing applications. Provides expertise on cloud implementation and researches emerging trends and technologies related to cloud engineering. Implements prescribed solutions for various deployment models and delivery models including Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), Platform as a service (PaaS), and Software as a Service (SaaS).  Prepares and updates documentation relating to organizational standards and procedures pertaining to the cloud.
